                approach_label: 'Our approach',
                approach_title: 'Four things we never compromise on.',
                pt1_h: 'We only observe.',
                pt1_p: 'Wildlife is never fed, handled, or disturbed. Every encounter happens on the animal\'s own terms — we slow down, keep quiet, and wait. The Amazon rewards patience far more reliably than noise.',
                pt2_h: 'Patience over speed.',
                pt2_p: 'We don\'t rush. The best encounters happen when you slow down, keep quiet, and wait — not when you follow a fixed schedule. We plan every trip around the forest\'s rhythm, not the clock.',
                pt3_h: 'Local, deep expertise.',
                pt3_p: 'Every guide is from Amazônia. Not transferred in from elsewhere, not following a standard itinerary for the first time. They know this specific river, this specific forest, the patterns of this particular season.',
                pt4_h: 'Community comes first.',
                pt4_p: 'Our trips pass through, and depend on, the communities that live along these rivers. We use local food suppliers, employ local labour, and share knowledge that comes from generations of people who called this place home long before we arrived.',
                cap1: 'In the field', cap2: 'Early morning on the Negro', cap3: 'Dawn on the Amazon',
