                stat_act_l: 'Activity Level', stat_act_v: 'Moderate',
                stat_grp_l: 'Group Size', stat_grp_v: 'Small & Private',
                intro_p: 'The <strong>Amazon Birdwatching</strong> tour is designed for serious birders and curious naturalists alike. Seven days moving through six distinct ecosystems — from the towering terra firme canopy of Ducke Reserve to the black-water igarapés of Anavilhanas National Park. Your guide is not a generalist: this is an ornithologist who has been birding the Amazon basin for decades, with an ear that catches a call before any telescope finds the canopy. Expect toucans, trogons, manakins, jacamars, raptors, and the iconic Amazonian Cock-of-the-Rock performing at its arena at dawn.',
